{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Dungeons & Dragons'' 3.5 edition monsters}} {{See also|List of Dungeons & Dragons monsters}} {{refimprove|date=October 2014}}
'''''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' version 3.5''' (see [[editions of Dungeons & Dragons|editions of ''Dungeons & Dragons'']]) was released in 2003. The first book containing monsters to be published was the ''[[Monster Manual]]'', released along with the other two "core" rulebooks.
==WTC 17755 – ''Monster Manual'' (2003)== This was the initial monster book for the ''Dungeons & Dragons'' [[Editions of Dungeons & Dragons#Dungeons & Dragons 3.5 edition|3.5 edition]], published in 2003. It includes all of the monsters from the [[List of Dungeons & Dragons 3.0 edition monsters#TSR 11552 – Monster Manual (2000)|previous third edition ''Monster Manual'']], revising them for the version 3.5 rules, as well as including a small number of monsters not in the previous ''Monster Manual''. This book features an alphabetical listing of monsters on pages 3–4, an introduction on pages 5–7, the monster descriptions on pages 8–289, instructions for improving the monsters in the book on pages 290–294 and making monsters on pages 295–302, skills and feats for monsters on pages 303–304, a glossary on pages 305–317, and a list of the monsters in the book ranked by challenge rating on pages 318–319.
{{ISBN|0-7869-2893-X}}
