==WTC 17741 – Lords of Madness (2005)== ''[[Lords of Madness]]: The Book of Aberrations'' was published in 2005, and written by [[Richard Baker (game designer)|Richard Baker]], [[James Jacobs (game designer)|James Jacobs]], and [[Steve Winter]]. Lords of Madness is an official supplement for the 3.5 edition of Dungeons and Dragons, and includes new content for [[Aberration (Dungeons & Dragons)|aberrations]]. The book contains a chapter on each of six types of monsters, some of which also feature statistics for that particular monster and/or its variants. In Chapter 8, statistics are given for new monsters, on pages 135–172.
{{ISBN|0-7869-3657-6}}
